.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
node_modules/

# Copilot CLI session transcripts can leak into the working dir if
# probe prompts reference filenames. Per `gh copilot -- --help`:
# - `--share[=path]` writes `copilot-session-<id>.md` (markdown) in
#   cwd by default
# - `--output-format json` writes JSONL to stdout (not a file)
# - `--log-dir <dir>` defaults to `~/.copilot/logs/` (outside repo)
#
# We ignore the `.md` form (the documented file leak vector) and
# keep the `.jsonl` form for defense-in-depth — an earlier real
# incident (commit 1fc8677) leaked `.deny-test.jsonl` /
# `.revparse-test.jsonl` from Copilot's own tool-permission probes
# that the current CLI may have renamed but could resurface. Keeping
# both prefixes narrow (no wildcard `*-test.jsonl` — that would hide
# legitimate fixtures).
#
# The PRIMARY prevention is the review-cycle docs' rule: review
# outputs go to /tmp, not the repo. These patterns are belt-and-
# suspenders.
copilot-session-*.md
.copilot-session-*.md
copilot-session-*.jsonl
.copilot-session-*.jsonl
